require(cluster)
require(factoextra)
require(pdist)
require(data.table)
require (glmnet)
require(ecodist)
require(pracma)

Euclidean Distance cluster=6

pam.data=pam(data[,3:168], 6, metric = "euclidean",diss=FALSE, stand = TRUE) #3lü clusteer da dene
fviz_cluster(pam.data, main = "Partitioning around Mediods")

medoids=as.matrix(pam.data$medoids)
data_euc=as.matrix(data)
distances=distmat(data_euc[,3:168], medoids)
matrix_distances=as.matrix(distances)
bag_dist=cbind(data[,1:2],matrix_distances)
bag_dist=data.table(bag_dist)
colnames(bag_dist)[colnames(bag_dist)=="V2"] <- "Bag"
all_mean=matrix(0,92,8)

for(i in 1:92)
{
    a=bag_dist[Bag==i]
    a_mean=colMeans(a[,3:8])
    all_mean[i,3:8]=a_mean
    all_mean[i,1]=as.matrix(a[1,1])
    all_mean[i,2]=as.matrix(a[1,2])
}

training_feature=all_mean[,3:ncol(all_mean)]

model=cv.glmnet(training_feature, all_mean[,1],nfolds=9,type.measure="auc", family="binomial" )
plot(model, main="Area Under ROC Curve for PAM with 6 clusters with Euclidean Distance ")

pam.data2=pam(data[,3:168], 2, metric = "euclidean",diss=FALSE, stand = TRUE) #3lü clusteer da dene
fviz_cluster(pam.data2, main = "Partitioning around Mediods")

medoids2=as.matrix(pam.data2$medoids)
data_euc2=as.matrix(data)
distances2=pdist2(data_euc2[,3:168], medoids2)
matrix_distances2=as.matrix(distances2)
bag_dist2=cbind(data[,1:2],matrix_distances2)
bag_dist2=data.table(bag_dist2)
colnames(bag_dist2)[colnames(bag_dist2)=="V2"] <- "Bag"
all_mean2=matrix(0,92,4)

for(i in 1:92)
{
    a2=bag_dist2[Bag==i]
    a_mean2=colMeans(a2[,3:4])
    all_mean2[i,3:4]=a_mean2
    all_mean2[i,1]=as.matrix(a2[1,1])
    all_mean2[i,2]=as.matrix(a2[1,2])
}

training_feature2=all_mean2[,3:ncol(all_mean2)]

model2=cv.glmnet(training_feature2, all_mean2[,1],nfolds=9,type.measure="auc", family="binomial" )
plot(model2,main="Area Under ROC Curve for PAM with 2 clusters with Euclidean Distance ")

Manhattan Distance cluster =6

Hierarchical Cluster with Euclidean Distance

data_hclust=as.matrix(data[,3:168])

fit <- hclust(dist(data[,3:168]), method="centroid")
plot(fit, main ="Hierarchical Clustering with Centroid Method" , hang=0.01, labels=NULL)

clusters = cutree((fit), k=6) # get 6 clusters

Hierarchical Cluster with Manhattan Distance

data_hclust=as.matrix(data[,3:168])

fit <- hclust(distance(data[,3:168], method="manhattan"), method="centroid")
plot(fit, main ="Hierarchical Clustering with Centroid Method" , hang=0.01, labels=NULL)

clusters = cutree((fit), k=6) # get 6 clusters
